===Definitions===
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# [[confused]]; [[puzzled]]; [[deluded]]
#: {{zh-x|大惑不解|much '''confused''', unable to explain}}
#* {{zh-x|ref=Lunyu|子 曰：「知 者 不 惑，仁 者 不 憂，勇 者 不 懼。」|The Master said, "The wise are not '''confused''', the benevolent do not worry, and the brave do not fear.}}
#* {{zh-x|ref=Zhuangzi|三 人 行 而 一 人 惑，所 適 者 猶 可 致 也，惑 者 少 也；二 人 惑 則 勞 而 不 至，惑 者 勝 也；而 今 也 以 天下 惑。|If three people walk and one of them is '''deluded''', they can still reach the place they are heading for; the '''deluded''' are in the minority. If two [of the three] are deluded, they will toil but never arrive; the '''deluded''' are in the majority. And today, All Under Heaven is '''deluded'''.}}
# to [[confuse]]; to [[delude]]; to [[mislead]]
#: {{zh-x|妖言惑眾|to speak deceit and '''delude''' the masses}}
#* {{zh-x|ref=Zhuangzi|此 六 子 者，世 之 所 高 也，孰 論 之，皆 以 利 惑 其 真 而 強 反 其 情性，其 行 乃 甚 可 羞 也！|These six lords are those who are honored by the world. Carefully consider them. They all '''muddled''' their genuineness for the sake of profit, and forced themselves to turn away from their inherent nature. Their actions are really to be ashamed of!}}
# {{lb|zh|literary}} to [[infatuate]]; to be [[obsessed]] with, to be [[infatuated]] with
# {{lb|zh|Buddhism}} [[sensory]] [[delusion]]

